events.name: Golden State Warriors at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo and the Milwaukee Bucks made sure coach Mike Budenholzer had an easy first night back on the job.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has triple-double, Bucks rip Warriors 118-99

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 21 points, Jaren Jackson Jr. added 20 and the Memphis Grizzlies pulled away in the final minutes for their 11th straight victory, beating the Minnesota Timberwolves 116-108 on Thursday night.

events.name: LA Clippers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 24 points and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Los Angeles Clippers 113-89 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Ingram has 24 points, Pelicans beat Clippers 113-89

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — James Harden had the look of a man who needed rest, even before explaining how he felt.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Dort lead Thunder past Nets, 130-109

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Will Barton had 21 points before leaving late in the third quarter with a strained neck, Nikola Jokic added 20 and the Denver Nuggets beat the depleted Portland Trail Blazers 140-108 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barton scores 21, Nuggets beat depleted Blazers 140-108
